    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.robots.jobs.list(asset_id?: string, limit?: number, page?: number, status?: 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'errored' | 'cancelled', workflow?: string): { id: string; _links: object; created_at: number; status: job_status; updated_at: number; workflow: string; }`\n\n**get** `/robots/v1/jobs`\n\nReturns a paginated list of Robots jobs, with optional filters for workflow, status, and asset_id.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `asset_id?: string`\n  Filter by Mux asset ID\n\n- `limit?: number`\n  Maximum number of jobs to return (default 25, max 100)\n\n- `page?: number`\n  Page number (default 1)\n\n- `status?: 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'errored' | 'cancelled'`\n  Filter by job status\n\n- `workflow?: string`\n  Filter by workflow name\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; _links: { self: { href: string; }; }; created_at: number; status: 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'errored' | 'cancelled'; updated_at: number; workflow: string; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `_links: { self: { href: string; }; }`\n  - `created_at: number`\n  - `status: 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'errored' | 'cancelled'`\n  - `updated_at: number`\n  - `workflow: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Mux from '@mux/mux-node';\n\nconst client = new Mux();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const jobSummary of client.robots.jobs.list()) {\n  console.log(jobSummary);\n}\n```",
